# CODEOWNERS — gitlore
#
# Source of truth for review routing on PRs. Note that gitlore is a solo
# project (Amit, sole maintainer) so the practical effect of CODEOWNERS is
# narrow: it pins **eval-grade artifacts** so they cannot be silently rewritten
# by an automated PR (ralph, dependabot, or a future contributor) without an
# explicit review from the data steward.
#
# Branch-protection ties this together via `tier:judgement`: any PR that
# touches a CODEOWNERS-pinned path is expected to carry the `tier:judgement`
# label, which forces green private CI + 1 approving review (see
# `docs/branch-protection.md` and ADR-028). The label is reviewer-applied, not
# automatic; CODEOWNERS surfaces the review request, branch-protection
# enforces the merge gate.
#
# Format: GitHub native CODEOWNERS. Last-matching rule wins per path.
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners
#
# References:
# - Open Question Q3 (fixture protection): the labeled eval set and the
#   risk/story labeled commit sets are the empirical foundation for M4/M8
#   acceptance gates. They must not drift without a deliberate review.
# - Spec §20 M4 (labeled eval set blocks M4) and §20 M8 (spicy/boring set
#   blocks M8).
# - ADR-028 (branch protection two-tier gate).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner — every path falls back to the sole maintainer until an
# explicit external contributor is added.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*                           @amit-t

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Q3 fixture protection — pinned eval-grade artifacts.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public labeled fixtures used by `cargo test` and the public eval lane.
qa/fixtures/**              @amit-t

# Private labeled fixtures used by the self-hosted `eval-regression` job
# (see `.github/workflows/ci.yml`). These typically live in a sibling private
# repo and are vendored in via submodule; the rule is here so that if they
# ever land in-tree they are pinned automatically.
qa/fixtures-private/**      @amit-t

# Steering documents — process rules, ADR conventions, ralph prompts.
# Treated as eval-grade because a silent rewrite changes how every downstream
# agent (ralph, reviewers, future contributors) interprets every artifact.
steering/**                 @amit-t

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supporting governance files — pinned for the same reason as steering/**.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/CODEOWNERS         @amit-t
/.github/workflows/**       @amit-t
/docs/branch-protection.md  @amit-t
/CONTRIBUTING.md            @amit-t
/LICENSE-MIT                @amit-t
/LICENSE-APACHE             @amit-t
